<Author>Berkshire_UK
<Content>A workhorse hotel Last stayed at this hotel in 2002 and it appears as if nothing has changed. I mean nothing. It is a typical well worn business hotel that is used by business people and tourists alike. It is now starting to look a bit old and worn.The rooms are quite small with basic Ikea style furniture and fittings. Everything worked ok and it was clean (not spotless). The bath had a curtain that didn't quite fit, so the carpet into the bedroom and the door frame were starting to rot away. Nothing serious but why has nobody from maintenance noticed?Stayed for 4 nights and one day the room wasn't cleaned. Not a big deal, but had to wait a further hour before someone from housekeeping came.Breakfasts were very good. Hot and cold to suit most tastes. Staff throughout the hotel were very good, polite, attentive, although I did come across a couple of waiters in the bar area that spoke NO English. Very unusual in a European business hotel, but it was fun to point and smile to ask for what you wanted.Location is good from airport. 20 mins and 20 Euros by taxi. Metro is right down the road and is very cheap. 5.50 Euro for a one day all you can eat ticket. You can walk to the Ramblas tourist area in about 30 mins, but it is worth getting the metro back. Watch out for pickpockets.....they are everywhere in Barcelona. No problem in the hotel though with security. 
