<Author>jamesprh
<Content>Great Hotel and friendly staff Stayed at this purposely because it is away from the city centre. Don't get me wrong, I love the city centre, but the hotel is far enough out to get you into an area of Barcelona called 'Corts'. The area is remarkably tourist free with great shopping on your door step. Placa Catalunyia is a brisk 25 minute walk away but you can be at the tourist bus stop (A definite must do!!) on Pl. de Francesc Macia in 10 minutes. Your nearest metro is 5 mins away it runs direct to Dressanes at the bottom of las Ramblas and takes 10 minutes.The hotel itself is your typical Hilton 5*. Modern rooms, air conditioning, TV etc. There has been criticism on room size. To be fair the rooms aren't the biggest I've stayed in but are more than adequate. We stayed on the executive floor and found the room sizes to be a standard size across all classes. The room was clean and the bathroom spotless. We found the staff to be very helpful and nothing was too much trouble. We stayed on the executive floor on a BB basis. If you stay on the executive floor continental breakfast is included provided you eat it the executive lounge (see comments below about Americans!). Our room rate included full breakfast in the main dinging room - far superior to what was offered upstairs!!The executive floor has its perks such as afternoon coffee and cake. About four thirty they open up the alcohol. Free pour spirits, selection of wines, beer and soft drinks. There are hot and cold nibbles also. One thing to be aware of is drunk Americans!! Ww've normally found Americans (we are British btw) to be quite anal over the volume of alcohol that other people drink. Not so when it's free!! Don't be surprised to see Americans knocking back the liquor and grazing off the buffet for most of the night. That is until they pass out through drink or go into a food coma from the sheer volume of food they have consumed leaving little for anybody else - well that is until the buffet is replenished and they descend on it like a plague of locusts. Enjoy we did. 
